HEADWORD: Demoralization
<hw>De*mor`al*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧moralisation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of corrupting or
subverting morals. Especially: The act of corrupting or subverting
discipline, courage, hope, etc., or the state of being corrupted or
subverted in discipline, courage, etc.; <as>as, the
<ex>demoralization</ex> of an army or navy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

